tinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png\" onerror=\"this.srcset='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.src='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.classList.remove('lazypreload'); \"><a class=\"pinit\" href=\"https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-pin=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/10\/23131137\/Moray-Terraces-sacred-valley-peru.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h3 id=\"h-ollantaytambo\">Ollantaytambo<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Ollantaytambo town is the last part of the Sacred Valley that&#x2019;s accessible by car. It is the starting point for many walking trails to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/peru\/machu-picchu\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Machu Picchu (opens in a new tab)\">Machu Picchu<\/a> and the world-famous train ride to Aguas Calientes (Machu Picchu town).&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><ul class=\"blocks-gallery-grid\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/10\/23131118\/Ollantaytambo-alpaca-608x810.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/noscript><img width=\"254\" height=\"338\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"17062\" data-link=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/?attachment_id=17062\" class=\"wp-image-17062 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 608px) 100vw, 608px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/10\/23131118\/Ollantaytambo-alpaca-608x810.jpg 608w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/10\/23131118\/Ollantaytambo-alpaca-300x400.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/10\/23131118\/Ollantaytambo-alpaca-600x800.jpg 600w, https:\/\/static.s